{
  "texts": [
    "Using Eq. 6, it can be given as below.• Prior Probability P(E): The probability of an extreme rainfall day, estimated from historical data (e.g., 5% of days in the past have experienced extreme rainfall).",
    "• Likelihood P(X 1∶T |E): The probability of observing the rainfall data X 1∶T under the assumption that an extreme event has occurred.",
    "This distribution could be characterized by using models tailored to extreme events, though GEV is specifically applicable to extremes rather than the complete time series.",
    "P(X 1∶T |E) is not being modeled directly using GEV.",
    "Instead, it is decomposed into,components that relate to extreme behavior and Components that relate to normal behavior."
  ]
}